The paper deals with a cognitive radio communication system, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The problem of maximizing the rate of the secondary user while keeping the interference power to the primary user below a threshold can be seen as a control and optimization problem, falling under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of multiple transmit antennas and a single receive antenna suggests that the paper may also involve signal processing and machine learning (cs.MM). Finally, the development of an analytical solution from a geometric perspective suggests that the paper may also involve geometry and topology (cs.LG).
